198
00:19:36,058 --> 00:19:39,440
The A+ Setup Scorecard
You now have all the pieces, but I'm going to show  

199
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:45,920
you how to put them together into a systematic 
approach that eliminates all the guesswork. 

200
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:52,400
I call this the A+ Setup Scorecard—your 
quality control system that separates  

201
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:56,480
opportunity from mediocrity.
Here's how it works. 

202
00:19:56,480 --> 00:20:00,757
Every potential trade gets scored on five 
criteria. You don't take the trade unless  

203
00:20:00,757 --> 00:20:04,160
it scores at least four out of five points.
Point one: Is the 1-hour chart trending?  

204
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:11,680
If price is clearly above or below the 50 EMA 
with clean market structure, you get one point. 

205
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:17,680
Point two: Is price testing a key 
support or resistance zone? If your  

206
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:23,920
pullback is happening at key level that has 
proven its importance, you get one point. 

207
00:20:23,920 --> 00:20:31,040
Point three: On the 5-minute chart, is price 
testing the VWAP inside that zone? If yes,  

208
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:38,640
you get one point. No VWAP test, no entry.
Point four: Is there Fibonacci confluence?  

209
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:45,680
If your VWAP test also lines up with the 
61.8% retracement level, you get one point. 

210
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:51,120
Point five: Do you have a clear outside 
candle signal? If the market is showing  

211
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:56,800
you strong rejection at your level 
with conviction, you get one point. 

212
00:20:56,800 --> 00:21:03,120
This scorecard eliminates emotional trading. 
You're not trading because you're bored or  

213
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:08,400
because you feel like you should be in the 
market. You're trading because the setup  

214
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:16,080
meets your criteria like a checklist for success.
A five-point trade is perfection. A four-point  

215
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:24,000
trade is excellent. A three-point trade is 
average. Anything below three points is a pass. 

216
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:30,000
Most traders take three-point trades and wonder 
why they're not making money. You're going  

217
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:35,520
to wait for four and five-point trades.
This is your filter for quality control.

218
